import React, { useState } from "react"; export default function Utilities() { const [clockLogs] = useState([ { id: 1, employee: "John Doe", type: "Clock In", time: new Date() }, { id: 2, employee: "Jane Smith", type: "Clock Out", time: new Date() }, ]); const [cashCounts] = useState([ { id: 1, totalAmount: 256, bills: { 100: 2, 50: 1, 20: 0, 10: 0, 5: 1, 1: 6 }, coins: { 1: 2, 0.5: 3, 0.25: 4, 0.1: 0, 0.05: 0, 0.01: 10 }, createdAt: new Date(), }, ]); const [refunds] = useState([ { id: 1, item: "Latte", amount: 5.5, createdAt: new Date() }, { id: 2, item: "Bagel", amount: 3.0, createdAt: new Date() }, ]); return (
{/* Clock In/Out */}

Clock In / Out

{clockLogs.map((log) => ( ))}
Employee Type Time
{log.employee} {log.type} {log.time.toLocaleString()}
{/* Cash Count */}

Cash Count

{cashCounts.map((count) => ( ))}
Total Bills Coins Time
${count.totalAmount} {Object.entries(count.bills) .filter(([_, v]) => v > 0) .map(([k, v]) => `${k}x${v}`) .join(", ")} {Object.entries(count.coins) .filter(([_, v]) => v > 0) .map(([k, v]) => `${k}x${v}`) .join(", ")} {count.createdAt.toLocaleString()}
{/* Refund */}

Refund

{refunds.map((ref) => ( ))}
Item Amount Time
{ref.item} ${ref.amount} {ref.createdAt.toLocaleString()}
); }
